		<div id="comment_body_64398192"><p><span class="substr"> </span> <em>That's to get something like freenet actually working.</em> </p><p>First of all; Centralization is not the only thing stopping replacement of Youtube.   Hosting and distributing large video files is expensive -- the large companies pay a huge dollar figure not only to host those files,  but also for network capacity to send those files.     Your average home user internet connection has a capped upstream, and even if the internet is decentralized, you aren't able to decentralize hosting of large video files.</p><p>The other tr</p></div>
